The paper proposes a new method for online change-point detection that relies on recursive statistics and leverages Random Features to efficiently use the Maximum Mean Discrepancy as a distance between distributions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ML), statistics (cs.ST), and information theory (cs.IT).
